cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.LG, cs.MM

This paper discusses strategies and schemes to reduce user power consumption in cellular networks, specifically in the context of IoT devices. This topic falls under the category of networked and distributed systems, which is covered by cs.NI (Networked and Distributed Systems). The paper also involves resource allocation and optimization, which is a common theme in information theory, covered by cs.IT (Information Theory). The use of algorithms and analysis of performance metrics suggests a focus on systems and control, covered by cs.SY (Systems and Control). Additionally, the paper involves machine learning and optimization techniques, which are covered by cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
